            }
          ],
          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# Step 3: Range-compressed — full view + x6-upsampled 0-centred crop.\n# The crop is 6x complex-upsampled (same as the focused crop) so the range\n# sinc sidelobes are smooth instead of stair-stepped at the native sampling.\nrg_axis = (t_r - t_r_center) * c / 2\n_W = PEAK_HALF * view_scale\n\n# (1) Full view\nsurface3d(s_rc, rg_axis, az_pos, 'Step 3: Range-compressed (full view)')\n\n# (2) x6 crop\n_rc = np.where((rg_axis >= -_W) & (rg_axis <= _W))[0]\n_ac = np.where((az_pos  >= -_W) & (az_pos  <= _W))[0]\n_sub = s_rc[_ac[0]:_ac[-1]+1, _rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]\n_rgx = rg_axis[_rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]; _azx = az_pos[_ac[0]:_ac[-1]+1]\nF = 6\n_mag = upsample_complex(_sub, F)\n_rgu = upsample_axis(_rgx, F); _azu = upsample_axis(_azx, F)\nsurface3d(_mag, _rgu, _azu, 'Step 3: Range-compressed (x6 crop)', status='upsample x6')\n",
            "label": "Plot: Range-compressed",
            "spec": "Display-only: 3-D dB surface of |s_rc| after range compression. Targets are now sharp in range (thin ridges) but still spread in azimuth. Peak-preserving max-pool downsample; Expand for full size."
          },
          "executionOrder": 24,
          "codeCollapsed": true
        },
        "width": 400,
        "style": {}
      },
      {
        "id": "n20",
