          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# Step 4: Range-Doppler — full view + range-only x6 crop. Vertical axis is\n# Doppler [Hz] (not metres), so only the range axis is cropped AND upsampled;\n# the Doppler axis is left as-is.\nrg_axis = (t_r - t_r_center) * c / 2\n_W = PEAK_HALF * view_scale\nsurface3d(S_rd, rg_axis, f_eta, 'Step 4: Range-Doppler (full view)', ylabel='Doppler [Hz]')\n_rc = np.where((rg_axis >= -_W) & (rg_axis <= _W))[0]\n_sub = S_rd[:, _rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]\n_rgx = rg_axis[_rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]\nF = 6\n_mag = upsample_complex_range(_sub, F)\n_rgu = upsample_axis(_rgx, F)\nsurface3d(_mag, _rgu, f_eta, 'Step 4: Range-Doppler (range x6 crop)', ylabel='Doppler [Hz]', status='upsample x6 (range)')\n",
            "label": "Plot: Range-Doppler",
            "spec": "Display-only: 3-D dB surface of |S_rd| in the Range-Doppler domain. A target's energy lies on the RCM parabola (curved ridge across range vs Doppler) — this is why RCMC is needed. Axes: range [m] x Doppler [Hz]. Max-pool downsample."
